rComments: Best professor at UofT.. The exam was easy if you knew your stuff, but it was definitely fair. No one said UofT was easy. Suck it up or back yo bags.

Dr. Baker is just an adorable old man. And he's hilarious. He clearly knows metabolism well and is enthusiastic about it. People who complain about his teaching style and questions should remember that this is METABOLISM. Knowing the pathways and cycles is basic. He's super creative with his analogies and his test questions were fair and creative.

An amazing professor, the material taught was directly on the test as long as you kept up with it, and drew those damn structures EVERY DAY. For an hour a day you put into this class, its a 4.0 you would get out.
Course needs to be brought into the 21st century.  Memorizing a million details from a book is NOT contructive (profs should read papers by piaget, gardner, etc. on teaching theory)

This course is like any other U of T Science course.  The content is ok but the tests have nothing to do with lecture/text/notes/tutorial.  There really needs to be more accountablility with respect to this... the prof is ok.. I liked his analogies
tests do not match course content
possibly the best lecturer in the course, highly creative questions on test....
very funny!
the best course in university. his tests are challenging BUT his lectures make it worth all the trouble!
it is almost impossible to understand how his questions come from his lectures
one of the best

I think he's the only professor who can actually make biochemistry fun, although he made us pay for his "fun lessons" with his super texas-chainsaw-masscre-like exam... So, you should either study til the cows come home, or take this course in the summer.  Still, a great prof, though.

Sure he teaches ok, but come on...doesn't Cousin Nimmo eventually get on your mind? Plus, that exam was stupid..tested on itsy bitsy details that didn't ask for understanding but was made to kill. Overall, I was not impressed ..he definitely needs to take courses on how to write fair tests.

He is a superb professor. His way of teaching is simply brilliant. His lectures are super interesting and packed(I mean PACKED)with materials. I think he's a genius. That being said, his test is SUPER HARD. Beware.
I simply hate him.His analogies are redundant and an  insult to my intelligence. Like other UfT profs, he does not teach, he banters on and on. He should be fired.

He is really good at presenting the content of the course. Makes it enjoyable, interesting, and understandable. His analagies can be a stretch at time but sometimes they are very effective. His test questions are very difficult though!...Overall his classes are well organized and informative.

Profs don't get much better than this.  The guy has won awards for his teaching, and you're definetly not bored to death by his lectures.  The material is hard, and he can't really do anything about it except make the classes enjoyable, which is a BIG HELP!!

of all the courses i took this year, this was the 2nd most painful to sit through.  the lectures were extremely boring, even more so than our textbook (which was a huge waste of money).  mr. baker was totally disorganized.  all in all, a horrible experience.
No Comments
Yuk Yuk's Comedy Club for Science Nerds.  Humours the students without sacrificing clarity or detail.  Difficulty was just right - challenging but for the right reasons.

He makes lectures relatively enjoyable with his side stories and energy. But his test is brutal (and in the end that is what counts). What he tells you you should know. And if he specifically tells you to know it...memorize it to the molecule.

He made biochem fun. You know what they say, a good prof can make any subject interesting. He is one of those profs. The material is not tough as long as you KEEP UP. He explains very clearly as long as you LISTEN. And the tests aren't too tough, as long as you DON'T CRAM.

inane analogies, tangential yet enthusiatic crazy rantings that go nowhere, but good all the same.   Just like the scientist from the simpsons, with extremely clear notes for MNU - so clear people don't show up.

Very funny lecturer! He used some crazy analogies that really helped you relate to the material and remember it. But the tests were a lot harder than you'd expect from someone with such relaxed teaching styles

This guys a dink.  His lectures are nothing more than him reading his notes peppered with some inane analogies.  His mind is in a whole different world than the rest of ours.  He is one of my least favourite people.

Though his test questions were a little bit difficult, they really required you to think outside the box.  Very funny, with interesting anecdotes and stories which (usually) help reinforce important concepts. Lectures weren't boring.  GOOD OVERALL!!!
No Comments

Excellent prof.  Helps students learn concepts by relating them to the real world.  Goes a little fast sometimes but he's still the best.  You can tell he loves what he's doing -the most important aspect of teaching.
His classes were entertaining and hilarious.  He explained concepts really well but his test question were still on the difficult side.  He is still one, if not, the best prof.
Most enthusiastic  Prof at U of T.  Never look at my watch during his lecture.

he's okay. but he appears much better than he is. he makes jokes and laughs, but in there somewhere he spends 10 minutes on B-oxidation and virtually no time on thinking. He needs less jokes and more clarity
He's an awesome prof.  You'll never look at ttc turnstiles the same way again =)
a very funny guy... his analogies made his lectures very interesting and engaging...
one of the best lecturers i've had. the way he describes platelet-activating factor with analogies to pizza boxes and the death-star... was so entertaining. highly recommend any courses with dr.baker

An amazing prof!  Makes everything fun and interesting with great analogies! Watch out for his tests though, the little details on his multiple choice may screw you up.  But overall, BCH210 is one of the best courses!
Very funny professor with interesting analogies. Gotta love his cousin Nimo. ;)
he is very nice and gives great analogies. He give NO NOTES, and his exams are extremely difficult.
excellent
Very clear and effective. Lectures very quickly. Make sure to take your notes and not just listen.
Best professor I ever had! I wish there were more like him.
funny, engaging and effective...just remember not to sit in first 3 rows
one of THE BEST profs ever, loved the sound effects with describing hemoglobin
He is cute with his sunglasses!  But he'll be nicer if he gives an easier exam
Best prof in the world! should have brought nimo to class
my little cousin nimo thought he was sexy
Wish more profs were like him!
Good at explaining, test was really hard
